data.value: Which dimensions to sum over. Ellipsis ('...') sums over all dimensions. If not specified, then all the common dimensions are summed over.

children.type_: ..., str or tuple of str, optional

data.value: Additional keyword arguments passed to numpy.einsum or dask.array.einsum
Generalized dot product for xarray objects. Like np.einsum, but provides a simpler interface based on array dimensions.
